<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 09 at 3:06PM MDT until June 09 at 3:45PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN UNION COUNTY...
At 305 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles northeast
of Grenville, or 21 miles east of Des Moines, moving southeast at 10
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Clayton Lake State Park.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
